The paper focuses on evaluating the effectiveness of a recommender system in an Ed-Tech application, which involves analyzing user behavior and engagement with the system. This falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to analyze the content of the recommendations, which falls under the category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms for recommendation, which falls under the categories of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of data collected from user interactions, which falls under the category of Cybernetics (cs.CY).
